Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Rare opportunity in this unique and easily identifiable building located in beautiful Downtown Dieppe. Local area attractions include the Dieppe Farmer's Market, the Wingate hotel, the Cultural Arts Centre, Dieppes Public Library and Place 1604. Retailers nearby include Maddie and Sofia, Copper Branch, Ton's Bistro, and Uni Financial Cooperation.
Roughly 2,000 sq. ft. at a prominent corner location with 24' of frontage. See the brochure for more details!

Terrasses du Marché, is the newest mixed-use community development currently under construction by DuParc Real Estate Group, located in the heart of the beautiful Downtown Dieppe. Inspired by the vibrant community, this development will consist of residential, retail and office space.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 211 Champlain Street (Suite 205) is an ideal office/clinical space situated in Dieppe’s Downtown Core within a professional complex and a few steps from amenities such as restaurants, banks, City Hall and business services. The property benefits from surface parking at the rear as well as service from municipal transit. Upper floor is easily accessible by an elevator from the modern lobby. The ground level includes a variety of retail and professional medical tenants.
